TITLE: Nuclear fusion just passed a major milestone: Generating more energy than used to create the reaction
SUMMARY: The National Lab and Department of Energy announced a nuclear reaction that generated more energy than was required to power it -- a first for humankind.

TITLE: Consumer prices rose less than expected in November, up 7.1% from a year ago
SUMMARY: The consumer price index was expected to increase 0.3% in November, according to Dow Jones estimates.

TITLE: Sam Bankman-Fried criminal charges unsealed: Conspiracy to defraud the U.S., wire fraud, securities fraud, and money laundering
SUMMARY: Federal prosecutors accuse FTX co-founder Sam Bankman-Fried of widespread fraud and violating campaign finance laws, a new indictment says.

TITLE: Binance temporarily halts withdrawals of stablecoin USDC as investor concerns mount after FTX collapse
SUMMARY: Changpeng Zhao, CEO of Binance, tweeted on Tuesday that the exchange is seeing an increase in withdrawals of USDC.

TITLE: Bank of England calls for 'urgent' global action after near-collapse of UK pension funds
SUMMARY: The Bank of England called for "urgent international action" from regulators after it was forced to rescue U.K. pension funds in September.

TITLE: European Union reaches landmark agreement on a pollution tax for imports
SUMMARY: The EU has a goal to cut greenhouse gas emissions by at least 55% by the year 2030, compared to 1990.

TITLE: Europe moves closer on limiting natural gas prices as Brussels looks to protect consumers
SUMMARY: Energy ministers of the EU are discussing details over a cap on natural gas prices, but diviosn over the policy remain.

TITLE: Rivian pauses plans to make electric vans in Europe with Mercedes-Benz
SUMMARY: Rivian said it remains open to exploring future work with Mercedes-Benz "at a more appropriate time."

TITLE: What do hotel 'star' ratings really mean? Here's a breakdown
SUMMARY: One hotel can be rated three, four and even five stars — that's because ratings are "not regulated in a consistent way across the industry," one insider says.

TITLE: China brings WTO case against U.S. and its sweeping chip export curbs as tech tensions escalate
SUMMARY: China initiated a dispute against the U.S. at the World Trade Organization over Washington's sweeping semiconductor export curbs.

TITLE: Blizzard seeks new partners to continue offering World of Warcraft in China
SUMMARY: Blizzard is set to discontinue game services in China from January 2023 after failing to renew a 14-year contract with Chinese gaming giant NetEase.

TITLE: European Parliament removes Eva Kaili as vice-president after Qatar corruption allegations
SUMMARY: The European Parliament on Tuesday ousted a lawmaker who was arrested over the weekend in an investigation into alleged bribes by Qatar.

TITLE: Antibiotics prices surge in UK amid Strep A outbreak, leaving drugstores 'footing the bill'
SUMMARY: Drugstores are warning of shortages of key antibiotics used to treat Strep A, as cases rise in the U.K.

TITLE: Copper prices — traditionally a barometer for the global economy — are expected to soar next year
SUMMARY: Copper — traditionally seen as a leading indicator of economic health because of its use in many sectors — has unsurprisingly had a rough year. Yet analysts expect a resurgence in 2023.

TITLE: United Airlines is buying at least 100 Boeing Dreamliners to replace aging wide-body jets
SUMMARY: The massive order is a big boost for Boeing from one of its largest customers.

TITLE: Elon Musk is no longer the richest person in the world
SUMMARY: Bernard Arnault is now the richest man in the world, dethroning Tesla CEO Elon Musk after a continued decline in Tesla share price, according to Forbes.

TITLE: India and Vietnam could benefit as chipmakers shift away from China
SUMMARY: The Biden administration's China chip curbs are prompting chipmakers to relocate production chains to neighboring countries, experts say.

TITLE: Indian and Chinese forces sustained injuries in clash, Indian defence ministry says
SUMMARY: Indian and Chinese troops engaged and sustained injuries at a disputed Himalayan frontier.

TITLE: Elon Musk booed by crowd after Dave Chappelle brings him on stage at comedy gig
SUMMARY: Tesla boss Elon Musk is facing criticism over his handling of Twitter since buying that social media platform. His tweets have angered Democrats, LGBTQ activists and others.

TITLE: Jim Cramer says three key deals helped the market rally on Monday
SUMMARY: Stocks rose on Monday ahead of the monthly consumer price index report set to release Tuesday and the Federal Reserve’s December meeting.

TITLE: Police in China arrest gang who laundered $1.7 billion via crypto even after Beijing's crackdown
SUMMARY: Police in China arrested 63 people accused of laundering as much as 12 billion Chinese yuan ($1.7 billion) via cryptocurrency Tether.

TITLE: Consumer inflation expected to have continued cooling in November but still high
SUMMARY: Consumer inflation likely cooled in November, but prices continue to rise at a still high rate, particularly for services.

TITLE: Microsoft buys near 4% stake in London Stock Exchange Group as part of 10-year cloud deal
SUMMARY: U.S. tech giant Microsoft on Monday announced a 10-year partnership with the London Stock Exchange and took a near 4% stake in the U.K. bourse operator.

TITLE: Inflation has peaked — but it's not returning to pre-Covid levels in 2023, Mastercard says
SUMMARY: It'll take a few years to return to 2019 levels, said David Mann of the Mastercard Economics Institute.

TITLE: Twitter Blue relaunches, now costs $11 per month if you subscribe from an iPhone
SUMMARY: Twitter relaunched its updated Twitter Blue subscription service Monday after the company's new owner Elon Musk pulled and delayed the launch in November.

TITLE: Trust between the West and Russia has been destroyed, NATO chief says
SUMMARY: Russia continues to pound Ukraine's energy infrastructure too with devastating consequences for civilians.

TITLE: GM, Stellantis rank as worst automakers for fuel efficiency, even amid EV push, EPA says
SUMMARY: Both automakers decreased their fuel economy and increased C02 emissions since the 2016 model-year, as did Hyundai Motor, Mazda and Volkswagen.

TITLE: SpaceX launches lunar lander for Japanese venture ispace, which aims to create an economy around the moon
SUMMARY: If successful, ispace would be the first private company to land on the moon – a feat previously accomplished by global superpowers.

TITLE: Iran executes second protester after rapid trial as EU plans more sanctions
SUMMARY: Iran has long held what activists and other governments say are sham trials in order to imprison or execute critics of the state.

TITLE: Bioscience firms Novozymes and Chr. Hansen to merge in biggest-ever Danish deal
SUMMARY: Novozymes and Chr. Hansen have agreed to merge in a massive deal for Europe's biotech sector.
